Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["#1_BloodGroupData", "Title",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.980445082683243*^9, 
  3.980445099529709*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"8a5a2cfc-9051-c640-862f-\
24b98cc9c9a4"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "> ",
 StyleBox["NotebookDirectory[]",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " -> Locates the directory of the wolfram notebook.\n\n> ",
 StyleBox["SetDirectory[]",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " -> fixes the directory of the notebook. \n\n> ",
 StyleBox["FileName[]",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " -> Locates the file with a particular name in the fixed directory.\n\n> ",
 StyleBox["Dimensions[]",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " -> Mandatory to check. ALWAYS\n\n> ",
 StyleBox["//TableForm ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "-> Displays a matrix in table form. \n\n> ",
 StyleBox["TableView[]",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " -> An alternative way to display data. \n\n> ",
 StyleBox["Tally[bloodtypelist[[2;;,2]]] ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "-> tallies the elements in list, listing all distinct elements together \
with their multiplicities. Helps attain the ",
 StyleBox["Absolute Frequency",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " as well. \n\n> ",
 StyleBox["Count[]",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " -> Access the absolute frequency of each blood group. \n\n> ",
 StyleBox["Join[{{\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Blood Group\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote],\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]frequency\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]}},frequBloodtype \
]//TableForm",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ": \[LineSeparator]-> Adds column names to the table. \[LineSeparator]\n> ",
 StyleBox["BloodTable=Join[{{\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Blood Group\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote],\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]frequency\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]}},Tally[bloodtypelist[[2;;,2]]],{{\
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]total\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote],Total[frequBloodtype][[2]\
]}} ]",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " -> Adds row at the end detailing the total number of samples and stores \
everything in a variable. \n\n> ",
 StyleBox["relfreq=counts/Total[counts] ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "-> calculates relative frequencies\n\n> ",
 StyleBox["BarChart[Tally[bloodtypelist[[2;;,2;;]]] [[All,2]], ChartLabels\
\[Rule]{  Tally[bloodtypelist[[2;;,2;;]]]   [[All,1]] } ] ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "-> Bar Chart that plots the absolute frequencies. \n\n> ",
 StyleBox["flist =",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " ",
 StyleBox["Select[bloodtypelist,#[[3]]\[Equal]\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]f\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]&][[All,2]]",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " -> Helps select a specific type of variable from the table. In this case \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]f\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]\n\n> ",
 StyleBox["Tally[Select[bloodtypelist,#[[3]]\[Equal]\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]f\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]&][[All,2]]] ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "-> Creates the absolute frequencies from a table. \n\n> ",
 StyleBox["PairedBarChart[flist[[All,2]],mlist[[All,2]],ChartLabels\[Rule]{\
flist[[All,1]] },PlotLabel\[Rule]\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]female       male\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]] ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "-> Creates a paired bar chart. \n\n> ",
 StyleBox["BarChart[{flist[[All,2]],mlist[[All,2]]},ChartLabels\[Rule]{flist[[\
All,1]] },ChartLayout->\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]Stacked\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]\
,PlotLabel\[Rule]\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]female       male\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]] ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "-> Creates a stacked bar chart. \n\n> ",
 StyleBox["BarChart[{flist[[All,2]],mlist[[All,2]]},ChartLabels\[Rule]{{\
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]female\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote],\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]\
male\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]},{flist[[1,1]],flist[[2,1]],flist[[3,1]],flist[[\
4,1]] }},ChartLayout->\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]Grouped\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]]\
 ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "-> creates a grouped bar chart. "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.980445118331072*^9, 3.980445252953087*^9}, {
  3.980445320469572*^9, 3.980445336870804*^9}, {3.9804453793035545`*^9, 
  3.980445411640896*^9}, {3.98044545037101*^9, 3.980445470727396*^9}, {
  3.980445507147522*^9, 3.9804455499789543`*^9}, {3.9804456099180927`*^9, 
  3.980445622337555*^9}, {3.9804457076076965`*^9, 3.9804458119507904`*^9}, {
  3.9804458597585926`*^9, 3.9804459328502064`*^9}, {3.980446110542225*^9, 
  3.980446133255287*^9}, {3.9804461851069927`*^9, 3.980446220494772*^9}, {
  3.9804464017634125`*^9, 3.9804465052992287`*^9}, {3.9804465442618294`*^9, 
  3.9804466522918396`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d5843003-0d39-2d43-bf9d-\
e4ace0116e13"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["#2_EnzymeData_GeyserData.nb", "Title",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9804467096144047`*^9, 
  3.9804467347906685`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"9d1ee428-bf88-cf4d-9d9e-\
eefe125ee10c"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "> Creating a frequency table: \n\n",
 StyleBox["STEP 1: ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "finding the ",
 StyleBox["Min[] ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "and ",
 StyleBox["Max[] ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "values to measure the size of the bins\n",
 StyleBox["Min[]",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " -> Finds the minimum value\n",
 StyleBox["Max[]",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " -> Finds the maximum value \n\n",
 StyleBox["STEP 2:",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "  Setting up and validating the structure of your frequency table before \
you actually build it.\n",
 "\n> ",
 StyleBox["BinCounts[enzyme, 10] ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "-> ",
 "counts how many data values from the enzyme dataset fall into each bin of \
width 10\n\n> ",
 StyleBox["Total[BinCounts[enzyme, 10]] ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "->",
 StyleBox[" ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "T",
 "hen simply sums all those bin counts together, which should equal the total \
number of data points in the dataset (n).\n\n> ",
 StyleBox["Ceiling[Min[enzyme[[2;;]]]-10,10] ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "-> You subtract 10 (the class width) from the minimum value first, giving a \
little buffer below the smallest data point. Ceiling[Min[enzyme[[2;;]]], 10] \
then rounds up to the nearest multiple of 10.\nThe result is a clean starting \
boundary that sits at or just below your minimum value, aligned to your class \
width grid.\n\n> ",
 StyleBox["Floor[Max[enzyme[[2;;]]]+10,10] ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "-> You add 10 to the maximum value, giving a little buffer above the \
largest data point. Floor[Max[enzyme[[2;;]]], 10] then rounds down to the \
nearest multiple of 10. The result is a clean ending boundary that sits at or \
just above your maximum value, aligned to your class width grid.\n\n> ",
 StyleBox["RR = Range[Ceiling[Min[enzyme[[2 ;;]]] - 10, 10], \
Floor[Max[enzyme[[2 ;;]]] + 10, 10], 10] ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "-> Using Range[] to actually generate the full list of boundaries with the \
help of Ceiling[] and Floor[] computing the starting and ending points. \n\n> \
",
 StyleBox["{RR[[#]], RR[[# + 1]], BinCounts[enzyme, 10][[#]]} & /@ Range[1, \
19]",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "-> Creates a list of paired class interval boundaries, essentially the \
lower and upper limit of each class interval. \n\n> ",
 StyleBox["BinLists[enzyme,10] ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "-> gives lists of the elements of data whose values lie in successive bins \
specified by binspec.\n\n",
 StyleBox["Step 3",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ": Calculating the relative frequency, density, Cumulative Relative \
frequency: \n\n>  ",
 StyleBox["relfreez = N[BinCounts[enzyme, 10]/Total[BinCounts[enzyme, 10]]] ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ":",
 StyleBox["\n",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "-> Calculates the relative frequency ",
 StyleBox["\n",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "-> ",
 StyleBox["BinCounts[enzyme, 10] ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "gives you the list of frequencies for each bin\n",
 StyleBox["Total[BinCounts[enzyme, 10]] ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "gives you the overall total ",
 StyleBox["(n)",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ". \n\n> ",
 StyleBox["densityez=relfreez/10 ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ": \[LineSeparator]-> Calculates the density\n\n> ",
 StyleBox["cumrelfreez=Accumulate[relfreez] ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ":\n-> Calculates the empirical cumulative distribution function/cumulative \
relative frequency. \n\n",
 StyleBox["Step 4",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ": Building a frequency table with bin min, bin max, absolute frequency, \
relative frequency, density and cumulative relative frequency. \n\n> ",
 StyleBox["enzymtable ={RR[[#]],RR[[#+1]],BinCounts[enzyme,10][[#]], \
relfreez[[#]], densityez[[#]], cumrelfreez[[#]]} &/@ Range[1,19]",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ": \n\n-> ",
 StyleBox["RR[[#]] ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "\[LongDash] the lower class boundary.\n-> ",
 StyleBox["RR[[# + 1]] ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "\[LongDash] the upper class boundary.\n-> ",
 StyleBox["BinCounts[enzyme, 10][[#]]",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " \[LongDash] the frequency count for that class.\n-> ",
 StyleBox["relfreez[[#]]",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " \[LongDash] the relative frequency for that class.\n-> ",
 StyleBox["densityez[[#]] ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "\[LongDash] the frequency density for that class.\n-> ",
 StyleBox["cumrelfreez[[#]]",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " \[LongDash] the cumulative relative frequency for that class.\n\n>",
 StyleBox["GRAPH TIPS:",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "\n\n-> If we select the option \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Probability\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote], we get the relative frequency: ",
 StyleBox["Histogram[enzyme[[2;;]],{20,220,10},\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]\
Probability\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]] \n",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "\n-> If we select the option \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]PDF\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote], we get the density (PDF means probability density \
function):",
 StyleBox[" Histogram[enzyme[[2;;]],{20,220,10},\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]PDF\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]] ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "\n\n-> If we select the option \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]CDF\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote], we get the cumulative relative frequency: ",
 StyleBox["Histogram[enzyme[[2;;]],{20,220,10},\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]CDF\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]] ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "\n\n-> We can also get the cumulative count: ",
 StyleBox["Histogram[enzyme[[2;;]],{20,220,10},\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]\
CumulativeCount\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]]",
  FontWeight->"Bold"]
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.980446739525812*^9, 3.9804467457410183`*^9}, {
   3.9804467878206825`*^9, 3.9804468224088936`*^9}, {3.9804469501558475`*^9, 
   3.9804469970816936`*^9}, {3.9804470697017517`*^9, 3.980447117270294*^9}, {
   3.9804474057322884`*^9, 3.980447427435173*^9}, {3.9804475555723553`*^9, 
   3.9804475668225803`*^9}, {3.980448130541546*^9, 3.9804482857764053`*^9}, {
   3.980448322018265*^9, 3.980448433092415*^9}, {3.9804485697724667`*^9, 
   3.980448627866356*^9}, {3.9804490312080593`*^9, 3.9804490619095917`*^9}, {
   3.9804491343006935`*^9, 3.980449179898653*^9}, 3.980449266352871*^9, {
   3.9804493376495705`*^9, 3.980449406536522*^9}, {3.980449500892578*^9, 
   3.9804495579180717`*^9}, {3.9804496186581345`*^9, 
   3.9804498638846664`*^9}, {3.9804498998447475`*^9, 
   3.9804499671371784`*^9}, {3.9804500339855423`*^9, 
   3.9804501466384125`*^9}, {3.980450230390585*^9, 3.9804502719463863`*^9}, {
   3.9804503145831394`*^9, 3.9804503288971653`*^9}, {3.9804503742573166`*^9, 
   3.9804505228013344`*^9}, {3.980450558617548*^9, 
   3.980450566139292*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"054eb449-a2e4-b246-9e21-\
8d48603e7bbd"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Measures of central tendency and dispersion", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9804505772288036`*^9, 
  3.980450582709757*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"4c0dd861-5695-814f-b406-\
3cac69f24ce7"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "> ",
 StyleBox["N[Mean[enzyme[[2;;]]]]",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " -> Calculates the mean\n\n> ",
 StyleBox["Median[enzyme[[2;;]]] ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "-> Calculates the median\n\n> ",
 StyleBox["Commonest[enzyme]",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " -> Calculates the mode\n\n> ",
 StyleBox["Quartiles[enzyme[[2;;]]]",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " -> Obtains the quartile. \n\n> ",
 StyleBox["BoxWhiskerChart[enzyme[[2;;]], \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Outliers\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]]",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " -> Makes a box whisker chart. Adding \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]outliers\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] gives you the outliers. \n\n> ",
 StyleBox["1.5*InterquartileRange[enzyme[[2 ;;]]] + Quartiles[enzyme[[2 \
;;]]][[3]] ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ": \n -> ",
 StyleBox["InterquartileRange[enzyme[[2;;]]]",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " calculates the IQR, which is ",
 StyleBox["Q3 - Q1 ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "\[LongDash] the spread of the middle 50% of the data.\n -> Multiplying by ",
 StyleBox["1.5",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " is the standard convention for defining how far beyond the quartiles a \
value can be before it\[CloseCurlyQuote]s considered an outlier.\n -> ",
 StyleBox["Quartiles[enzyme[[2;;]]][[3]] ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "extracts Q3 (the third quartile) from the list of quartiles.\n -> So the \
full expression is simply",
 StyleBox[" Q3 + 1.5\[Times]IQR",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ", which gives you the upper fence. ",
 StyleBox["Q1 - 1.5\[Times]IQR",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ", which you\[CloseCurlyQuote]d expect to see calculated in a companion line \
of code.\n \n > ",
 StyleBox["N[Variance[geyser[[2;;]]]]",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " -> calculates the variance\n \n > ",
 StyleBox["StandardDeviation[geyser[[2;;]]] ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "-> Calculates the standard deviation\n \n > ",
 StyleBox["N[Sqrt[Variance[geyser[[2 ;;]]]]]",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " -> Standard deviation is just the square root of variance.  "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9804505940040874`*^9, 3.9804506211645145`*^9}, {
  3.980450660245693*^9, 3.980450817364584*^9}, {3.980450850517868*^9, 
  3.9804510417433357`*^9}, {3.9804510750840874`*^9, 
  3.980451148998703*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"81530dd7-3d9c-6341-a9d6-\
13b751d6f83a"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["#3_Anscombe.nb", "Title",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.980451168350788*^9, 
  3.980451175262396*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"df140a6a-08d2-ea48-8001-\
bf5a5c4953d8"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "> ",
 StyleBox["LinearModelFit \n",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "\n> ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"set1", "=", 
    RowBox[{"anscombe", "[", 
     RowBox[{"[", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"2", ";;"}], ",", 
       RowBox[{"1", ";;", "2"}]}], "]"}], "]"}]}], ",", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"set2", "=", 
     RowBox[{"anscombe", "[", 
      RowBox[{"[", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"2", ";;"}], ",", 
        RowBox[{"3", ";;", "4"}]}], "]"}], "]"}]}], ";"}]}]], "Input",
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.7814225944399633`*^9, 3.781422604546073*^9}},
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"0847ec2d-2657-a141-a8d8-970bb9e64cef"],
 StyleBox[" ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"set3", "=", 
    RowBox[{"anscombe", "[", 
     RowBox[{"[", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"2", ";;"}], ",", 
       RowBox[{"5", ";;", "6"}]}], "]"}], "]"}]}], ";"}]], "Input",
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.781422610066222*^9, 3.781422622048135*^9}},
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"0fd3ff95-d4fe-864b-9d18-586f4b215ac5"],
 StyleBox[" ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"set4", "=", 
    RowBox[{"anscombe", "[", 
     RowBox[{"[", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"2", ";;"}], ",", 
       RowBox[{"7", ";;", "8"}]}], "]"}], "]"}]}], ";"}]], "Input",
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.781422644426537*^9, 3.781422650021688*^9}},
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"245e01c3-d3f0-5b4f-80e8-7d19f4e1ea77"],
 " -> Create pairs of values for the LinearModelFit and graph. \n\n> ",
 StyleBox["lms1=LinearModelFit[set1,x,x], lms2=LinearModelFit[set2,x,x], \
lms3=LinearModelFit[set3,x,x], lms4=LinearModelFit[set4,x,x]",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " -> Creates the fitted model. \n\n>",
 StyleBox["{lms1[\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]RSquared\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]],\
lms2[\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]RSquared\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]],lms3[\
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]RSquared\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]],lms4[\
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]RSquared\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]]} ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "-> retrieves the R squared values from four different linear model fits \
into a single list for easy comparison. \n\n>",
 StyleBox[" Show[{Plot[lms1[x],{x,2,20}],ListPlot[set1  \
,PlotStyle\[Rule]{Red,PointSize[0.03]}]}] ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "-> Creates a plot for the linear model fit. \n\n> ",
 StyleBox["Show[Plot[lms2[x],{x,2,20},PlotStyle->Blue,PlotLegends->{\
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]lms2\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]}],Plot[altlms2[x],{x,2,20}\
,PlotStyle->Gray,PlotLegends->{\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]altlms2\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]}],Plot[sugg2,{x,2,20},PlotStyle->Orange,PlotLegends->\
{\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]sugg2\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]}],ListPlot[set2  \
,PlotStyle\[Rule]{Red,PointSize[0.03]},PlotLegends->{\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]\
data\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]}]]",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ": \n\n> ",
 StyleBox["Plot[lms2[x], {x,2,20}, PlotStyle->Blue, PlotLegends->{\
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]lms2\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]}]",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " \[LongDash] plots the first fitted model lms2 as a blue curve over the \
range x=2 to x=20.\n> ",
 StyleBox["Plot[altlms2[x], {x,2,20}, PlotStyle->Gray, PlotLegends->{\
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]altlms2\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]}] ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "\[LongDash] plots an alternative version of the same model altlms2 as a \
grey curve over the same range.\n> ",
 StyleBox["Plot[sugg2, {x,2,20}, PlotStyle->Orange, PlotLegends->{\
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]sugg2\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]}]",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " \[LongDash] plots a suggested or manually proposed model sugg2 as an \
orange curve over the same range.\n> ",
 StyleBox["ListPlot[set2, PlotStyle->{Red, PointSize[0.03]}, PlotLegends->{\
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]data\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]}]",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " \[LongDash] plots the actual raw data points from set2 as large red dots."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.980451504820883*^9, 3.9804518449994297`*^9}, 
   3.980451891873459*^9, 3.9804519535493736`*^9, {3.9804520994967976`*^9, 
   3.9804521451633415`*^9}, {3.9804525389282436`*^9, 
   3.980452539385063*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"5c62af32-ca5f-7743-afd9-\
b82a829f01b2"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["#4_Correlation.nb", "Title",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9804525424521904`*^9, 
  3.980452555243065*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"dc7dcce6-da2a-254d-897e-\
82e07dc279f9"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "> ",
 StyleBox["Correlation[",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 StyleBox["v",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 StyleBox[",",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 StyleBox["w",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 StyleBox["]",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " -> The Bravais-Pearson correlation coefficient, gives the correlation \
between the vectors ",
 StyleBox["v",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " and ",
 StyleBox["w",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ". \n>  ",
 StyleBox["set4 = {#, # + RandomVariate[NormalDistribution[0, sigma]]} & /@ \
Range[0, 1, 0.0001] ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ": \n> ",
 StyleBox["Range[0, 1, 0.0001] ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "-> generates a sequence of x-values from 0 to 1 in steps of 0.0001, giving \
you 10,001 evenly spaced points.\n> ",
 StyleBox["{#, # + RandomVariate[NormalDistribution[0, sigma]]}",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " -> for each x-value (#), creates a pair {x, y} where:\n\t> The x-value is \
just #\n\t>The y-value is # plus a random noise term drawn from a normal\
\[LineSeparator]\t   distribution with mean 0 and standard deviation sigma\n> \
",
 StyleBox["& /@",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " -> applies this to every value in the range.\n> ",
 StyleBox["RandomVariate[] ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "-> Gives a list of n pseudorandom variates from the symbolic distribution \
dist.\n>",
 StyleBox[" SpearmanRho[geyser[[2;;,1]],geyser[[2;;,2]]]",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " -> Calculates the Spearman\[CloseCurlyQuote]s correlation coefficient."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9804525571354923`*^9, 3.9804526146814976`*^9}, {
  3.980452647594387*^9, 3.980452725555237*^9}, {3.980452867848686*^9, 
  3.980452982808775*^9}, {3.9804530918048344`*^9, 3.9804531128590374`*^9}, {
  3.9804531623996754`*^9, 
  3.980453203588516*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"b7c0d577-60ad-6241-b3f7-\
721ecb05cd63"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["#5_Distributions_implementation.nb", "Title",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.980453207903368*^9, 
  3.9804532216799297`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"6f517ce1-241e-604a-9b73-\
d6f2f0f5c3d9"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "> ",
 StyleBox["trials100=Table[RandomInteger[{1,6}],{100}] ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "-> Helps simulate rolling the die 100 times. \n\n> ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"p", "=", 
   FractionBox[
    RowBox[{"Count", "[", 
     RowBox[{"trials100", ",", "6"}], "]"}], "100"]}]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.7796870153351793`*^9, 3.779687049380246*^9}, {
    3.947751605621523*^9, 3.9477516106971292`*^9}, 3.9804533574681206`*^9},
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"e0a16678-0cdb-5741-96dc-eb5828479a84"],
 " or ",
 StyleBox["p=N[Count[trials100,6]/100]",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "-> The probability of success is estimated by the fraction of people \
obtaining a prize.  "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9804533056482754`*^9, 3.980453329013403*^9}, {
   3.980453370905079*^9, 3.9804534143852787`*^9}, {3.9804534605872116`*^9, 
   3.980453501672798*^9}, 
   3.9804536594225254`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"04d84d78-d95f-e848-9217-\
9b539dab206e"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["The Bernoulli distribution in Wolfram Language", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.9804535107760143`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"6fc8bf97-038f-f045-a86c-\
2bc16c359961"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "> ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   TemplateBox[{
     Cell[
      TextData["BernoulliDistribution"]], "paclet:ref/BernoulliDistribution"},
    "RefLink",
    BaseStyle->{"InlineFormula"}], "[", 
   StyleBox["p", "TI"], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontFamily->"Source Sans Pro",
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"f5bb376e-9b9f-814d-8ed8-e46e647e4b67"],
 " -> represents a Bernoulli distribution with probability parameter ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["p", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontFamily->"Source Sans Pro",ExpressionUUID->
  "0adaaf28-bdfe-314d-b000-8af6e93be6ee"],
 ".\n\n> ",
 StyleBox["PDF[BernoulliDistribution[1./6.],0] ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "-> Calculates the probability of failure (k=0) or success (k=1) of the \
experiment."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9804535142850266`*^9, 3.980453577813452*^9}, {
  3.980453655126446*^9, 
  3.9804536561198997`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"52fc01ab-98ed-c949-8249-\
f48fc78c05c6"]
}, Open  ]],

